HEADWORD: Amphora
<hw>Am"pho*ra</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Amophor⟦ae⟧</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<grk>'amforey`s</grk>, <grk>'amforey`s</grk>, a jar with two handles;
<grk>'amfi`</grk> + <grk>forey`s</grk> bearer, <grk>fe`rein</grk> to
bear. Cf. <er>Ampul</er>.]</ety> <def>Among the ancients, a two-handled
